# Client component structure

## Feature-first
- UI lives under `client/src/features/<feature>/components/<Name>/` with `index.tsx` + `<Name>.styles.ts`.
- Route screens under `client/src/features/<feature>/pages/` (e.g. `LoginPage.tsx`).
- Feature-specific helpers: `client/src/features/<feature>/lib/`.

## Shared
- Reusable primitives: `client/src/shared/components/<Name>/`.
- Cross-cutting helpers: `client/src/shared/lib/`.

## Stories
- **Storybook 8** is installed in `wedding-hall-client`. Co-locate `*.stories.tsx` next to the component (`index.tsx` + `*.styles.ts` in the same folder), or next to `*Page.tsx` for pages.
- Sidebar groups: **`Common/*`** (shared primitives), **`Features/*`**, **`Pages/*`** (route-level screens). Use `parameters.auth` (`"loggedIn"` or omitted) and `parameters.router.initialEntries` from `.storybook/preview.tsx` for auth + routing.
- API calls in stories hit **MSW** (`msw-storybook-addon` + `src/storybook/msw/handlers.ts`). Supabase in Storybook is replaced via Vite alias to `src/storybook/mocks/supabase-client.ts` — no real project keys required for layout work.
- Scripts: `npm run storybook` / `npm run build-storybook` from the repo root (workspace), or `-w wedding-hall-client`.

## Styling
- Global CSS tokens and layout live in `client/src/styles/style.css` (`wh-*` classes).
- **`*.styles.ts` files:** export only class name strings composing `wh-*` names; JSX uses those exports (arrays + `filter(Boolean).join(" ")` is fine).
